    "body": "> Please install the [gitoxide-cli](https://github.com/GitoxideLabs/gitoxide?tab=readme-ov-file#installation), and run gix status to help locating the offending file and to determine if there is a compatibility issue with the git-cli.\n\nIndeed, `gix status` lists this one file. I don't think I have touched that file in 2 years or so. It does have an emoji in the filename though. (However, I have various other files with emoji in the filename in that repo, and they never made a problem. Neither did this file, until last week.)\n\n```\n17:08:59 status done 1.6K files in 0.01s (242.3K files/s)\n ? Teaching/🎥 Überwachung im digitalen Zeitalter.md\n```\n\n> Does switching to the git-exe backend for the git_status module solve this issue?\n\nindeed, it does.\n\n",
