    "updated_at": "2025-08-11T12:23:10Z",
    "body": "Was seeing recently introduced, similar behavior of the Git prompt always showing `[?]`. Seems related to `gitignore` handling in my case.\n\n```console\n$ git status --untracked-files=all\nOn branch main\nYour branch is up to date with 'origin/main'.\n\nnothing to commit, working tree clean\n\n$ gix status\n 08:15:02 status done 8.9K files in 0.05s (187.4K files/s)\n  ? zSDKs/sdk-ruby/sorbet/rbi/annotations/\n  ? zSDKs/sdk-ruby/sorbet/rbi/gems/.gitattributes\n  ? zSDKs/sdk-ruby/sorbet/rbi/gems/base64@0.3.0.rbi\n  ? zSDKs/sdk-ruby/sorbet/rbi/gems/erubi@1.13.1.rbi\n  ? zSDKs/sdk-ruby/sorbet/rbi/gems/faraday-multipart@1.1.0.rbi\n  ? zSDKs/sdk-ruby/sorbet/rbi/gems/faraday-net_http@3.4.0.rbi\n  ? zSDKs/sdk-ruby/sorbet/rbi/gems/json@2.8.2.rbi\n  ? zSDKs/sdk-ruby/sorbet/rbi/gems/language_server-protocol@3.17.0.4.rbi\n  ? zSDKs/sdk-ruby/sorbet/rbi/gems/lint_roller@1.1.0.rbi\n  ? zSDKs/sdk-ruby/sorbet/rbi/gems/logger@1.6.6.rbi\n  ? zSDKs/sdk-ruby/sorbet/rbi/gems/minitest-focus@1.4.0.rbi\n  ? zSDKs/sdk-ruby/sorbet/rbi/gems/multipart-post@2.4.1.rbi\n  ? zSDKs/sdk-ruby/sorbet/rbi/gems/net-http@0.6.0.rbi\n  ? zSDKs/sdk-ruby/sorbet/rbi/gems/parallel@1.26.3.rbi\n  ? zSDKs/sdk-ruby/sorbet/rbi/gems/parser@3.3.7.1.rbi\n  ? zSDKs/sdk-ruby/sorbet/rbi/gems/prism@1.4.0.rbi\n  ? zSDKs/sdk-ruby/sorbet/rbi/gems/rack@3.1.11.rbi\n  ? zSDKs/sdk-ruby/sorbet/rbi/gems/regexp_parser@2.10.0.rbi\n  ? zSDKs/sdk-ruby/sorbet/rbi/gems/rubocop-minitest@0.37.1.rbi\n  ? zSDKs/sdk-ruby/sorbet/rbi/gems/tapioca@0.16.11.rbi\n  ? zSDKs/sdk-ruby/sorbet/rbi/gems/thor@1.3.2.rbi\n  ? zSDKs/sdk-ruby/sorbet/rbi/gems/unicode-display_width@3.1.4.rbi\n  ? zSDKs/sdk-ruby/sorbet/rbi/gems/unicode-emoji@4.0.4.rbi\n  ? zSDKs/sdk-ruby/sorbet/rbi/gems/uri@1.0.3.rbi\n  ? zSDKs/sdk-ruby/sorbet/rbi/gems/yard-sorbet@0.9.0.rbi\n\n$ git check-ignore -v zSDKs/sdk-ruby/sorbet/rbi/annotations/\nzSDKs/sdk-ruby/.gitignore:6:sorbet/\tzSDKs/sdk-ruby/sorbet/rbi/annotations/\n\n$ git check-ignore -v zSDKs/sdk-ruby/sorbet/rbi/gems/.gitattributes\nzSDKs/sdk-ruby/.gitignore:6:sorbet/\tzSDKs/sdk-ruby/sorbet/rbi/gems/.gitattributes\n```\n\nAdding this in `~/.config/starship.toml` as mentioned above resolves the prompt issue for me locally:\n\n```\n[git_status]\nuse_git_executable = true\n```\n",
