    "body": "> I just ran a test and the file also creates a problem in a test repo.\n> \n> However, the Problem is apparently not the emoji, but rather the German diacritic `Ü`. Removing it from the filename fixes the issue, adding it back makes the issue re-appear.\n\nThanks for the follow-up @chrisgrieser! Could you also validate that `core.precomposeUnicode` is enabled for that repository?\nIf so, it should be easy to reproduce.\nIt is, however, not trivially reproducing as the comment above might suggest - I tried and it seems to work fine. I created an Umlaut with the Finder though, so maybe there is more to it. It would be easiest to share slimmed down repository itself, zipped.",
