    "updated_at": "2025-08-18T21:31:02Z",
    "body": "I'm running into a similar problem, where I see the file modified `!` indicator is wrong (both false positive and false negatives).  Running `gix status`, it fails on a random one of our git submodules.  I'm guessing hashmap randomization causes the order of the output to change between runs.\n\n```\n[nix-shell:~/devel/project]$ gix status\n  M README.md\nError: Could not determine status for submodule at 'chest'\n\nCaused by:\n    A working tree is required to perform a directory walk\n\n[nix-shell:~/devel/project]$ gix status\nError: Could not determine status for submodule at 'redacted/test_with_setup_attribute'\n\nCaused by:\n    A working tree is required to perform a directory walk\n```\n\nEnabling `use_git_executable` fixes the problem.  Let me know if I should open a new issue.",
