    "created_at": "2025-09-04T08:51:19Z",
    "updated_at": "2025-09-04T08:51:19Z",
    "body": "I've had this issue for a while, too.\n\nI decided to finally look into it and in my case, the reason is that `gitoxide` doesn't seem to handle the `core.excludesFile` git setting. In the repo's `.git/config` file I've set said setting to `.mygitignore`: `git` correctly ignores the files listed in `.mygitignore` when calculating the status, but `gitoxide` sees these as new, untracked files.\n\nResolved the issue by removing the private ignore file since it'd become redundant in this particular repository (the files are now ignored in the main `.gitignore`).\n\nJust a FYI in case anyone else happens upon the same issue.",
    "author_association": "NONE",
    "pin": null,
